The '''Well of the World Brain''' was the name of the [[Senate Building/Legends|Senate Building]] after it was converted to house the [[World Brain]] of [[Coruscant/Legends|Yuuzhan'tar]].

Shaped like a [[Yuuzhan Vong]] skull, the metals of the Building were digested by [[yorik coral]], going deep underground, and providing the Well with an impenetrable wall, capable of surviving [[Concussion missile/Legends|concussion missiles]] and orbital bombardment&mdash;possibly even a planetary explosion, allowing the World Brain to survive as a self contained vessel. A [[hedge maze]] of ceremonial trees lined the front entrance to the Well. The trees were as resilient as [[Durasteel/Legends|durasteel]], and contained toxin filled needles ranging in size from a thumb to a forearm.

During [[Darth Caedus|Jacen Solo's]] sham attempt to sacrifice [[Ganner Rhysode]] to the World Brain, Ganner [[Battle of the World-Well|fought off]] scores of [[Warrior caste|Yuuzhan Vong Warriors]], becoming a legend to both the [[Jeedai heresy|''Jeedai'' heretics]] and the Warrior caste alike. During the [[Battle of Yuuzhan'tar]], [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]], [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa Solo]], and the [[Priest/Legends|Priest]] [[Harrar]] went to the Well in an attempt to prevent the World Brain from destroying [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].

